===Pronunciation===
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /'/
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /hIm/

===Personal pronoun===
'''him''' (objective case)
#[[he]] when used after a preposition or as the object of a verb
#:Give it to him (after preposition)
#:She wrote him a letter (indirect object)
#:She treated him for a cold (direct object)

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[hem]] ''f''
*French: (''after preposition'') [[lui#French|lui]], (''indirect object before a verb'') lui, (''indirect object after the verb'') à lui, (''indirect object with an imperative verb'') lui, (''direct object'') le (''becoming'' l' ''before a vowel or an mute h'')
*:'''Examples:'''
*::'''After preposition:''' It is for him - ''C'est pour lui''
*::'''Indirect object before a verb:''' She tells him her name - ''Elle lui dit son nom''
*::'''Indirect object after a verb:''' She gives the book to him - ''Il donne le livre à lui''
*::'''Indirect object with an imperative verb:''' Give it to him - ''Donnez-le-lui''
*::'''Direct object:''' She hates him - ''Elle le déteste''
*::'''Direct object before a vowel:''' She loves him - ''Elle l'aime''
*[[Frisian]]: him
*[[Guarani]]: [[i]]
*[[Interlingua]]: [[le]] (direct/indirect object); [[ille]] (after preposition)
*Italian: (''after preposition'') [[lui#Italian|lui]], (''indirect object before a verb'') [[gli]], (''indirect object with an imperative verb'') gli (''attached to the end of the verb and becoming'' [[glie]] ''when used along with a direct object''), (''direct object'') [[lo#Italian|lo]] (''becoming'' [[l']] ''before a vowel'')
*:'''Examples:'''
*::'''After preposition:''' It is for him - ''É per lui''
*::'''Indirect object before a verb:''' Maria tells him her name - ''Maria gli dice il suo nome''
